.TH UVPROTERMBT 1 "2026-07-19" "UVProTermBT 0.9.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
uvprotermbt \- AX.25 packet messenger + terminal for the BTech UV-Pro / VGC VR-N76
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B uvprotermbt
.RI [ --version ]
.br
.B uvprotermbt
.RI [ --help ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
UVProTermBT is a desktop AX.25 packet messenger and terminal for the
BTech UV-Pro / VGC VR-N76 ("Benshi" radio family). It talks to the radio's
built-in KISS TNC over classic Bluetooth (no cable, no external TNC) via
BlueZ's SerialPort profile.
.PP
It provides five modes in one PyQt6 window:
.TP
.B Chat
SMS-style APRS messaging (send/receive, auto-ack).
.TP
.B APRS
Live monitor of decoded AX.25 traffic and a heard-stations list.
.TP
.B BBS
A full AX.25 connected-mode terminal (connect to BPQ/nodes).
.TP
.B Winlink
Brings up the kernel AX.25 port and embeds PAT's web UI in-window.
.TP
.B SSTV
Send and receive images over the radio's Bluetooth audio channel (Robot36
and more).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Show a brief help message.
.SH FIRST RUN
On first launch a setup wizard asks for your callsign and lets you pick your
paired radio. On the radio itself, enable KISS TNC first:
Settings \(-> General Settings \(-> KISS TNC \(-> Enable KISS TNC, then pair
the radio to this computer.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/uvprotermbt/config.json
Per-user settings (callsign, SSID, Bluetooth MAC, APRS path, theme).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/uvprotermbt/sstv/
Saved received SSTV images.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B QTWEBENGINE_DISABLE_SANDBOX
Set to 1 by the app's startup shim (the pip-wheel WebEngine chrome-sandbox
is usually not setuid-root and crashes the renderer). The embedded page is
PAT's local UI on localhost, so this is an acceptable trade-off.
.TP
.B LD_LIBRARY_PATH
Augmented by the startup shim to include PyQt6's Qt6/lib so
PyQt6-WebEngine's sibling Qt libs load.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B uvprotermbt
Launch the GUI. First run walks you through setup.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pat (1),
.BR kissattach (8),
.BR bluetoothctl (1)
